Color in life— Sexual dichromatism present (
Fig. 2–4
). Dorsal head in males, black or dark brown; gray or brown in females, but never darker than males. Dorsum and sides of the body intense yellow or dark orange, with large paravertebral spots transverse to the body axis, divided on the sides of the body (
Fig. 2
). Paravertebral spots black or dark brown, band-shaped. In females the dorsal background is gray or reddishbrown. Without vertebral line, dorsolateral stripes nor scapulars spots. In males the tail is dorsally light gray or greenish-gray. Ventrally yellow or intense orange from the mental scale to the cloacal region, the tail ventrally exhibit same color of dorsum (
Fig. 3
). Females exhibit the same pattern but lighter (
Fig. 4
).
